					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12769101#post-4411351</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12769101/scp-4829#post-4411351</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 31 Oct 2019 23:56:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>The Great Hippo</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3938622</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is&#8230; hm.</p> <p>I like what you're going for, and I like the imagery in the log; there's a few mild formatting quips, but none of it is a deal-breaker. I think the main obstacle for me is that the pacing feels&#8230; off. As soon as I hit 'cytoplasm', I knew where this was going &#8212; and what ensued felt like it was rushing to get there.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Spoilers?</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>I'm not going to tell you this should be a slow-rolling atmospheric piece where we learn that the moon is undergoing cellular division piece by dreadful piece, because I know that ain't your thing &#8212; but I feel like the cellular aspects should either be better hidden or there should be an even weirder twist by the end to surprise the reader (like the moon impregnating another moon, or the phenomenon spreading &#8212; or maybe an answer to the question, &quot;okay, so what <em>impregnated</em> the moon?&quot;)</p> <p>Regardless, the idea of cosmic, celestial bodies being zygotes is pretty metal &#8212; and though I'm not upvoting, I'm certainly not <em>downvoting</em>.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p><strong>ETA:</strong> Added a collapsible, just in case.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
